Liber 1
The Saxon Poet's Vta Carol, Liber 1
Compiled by Aaron Decker
Aaron Decker
A Latin Reader in Two Levels
The Saxon Poet's Vta Carol Liber 1 is a narrative, set in heroic
verse, about Charlemagne's actions between 771 AD and 780 AD.
It was written by a Saxon poet sometime in 888-891 AD. It details
Charlemagne's unification of the Frankish realm and his military
campaigns with the Saxons, Lombards, and Basques.
This is a Latin reader intended for beginning and intermediate
students, so every page of Latin text has a full glossary on the
facing page. Extensive footnotes explaining any difficult grammar
or concepts are included with the original Latin text. The text is
highly legible (it is not photocopied) and has macrons. A set of
maps is provided in the back of the book. There is also a
simplified prose version to ease students into the original text.
